1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
I'm hungry.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Movie Monday!

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:16,000
The only cure I know for the Monday blues is...

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,000
varsity blues.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Let's go!

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Let's go!

8
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Everybody here?

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Yes.

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Where's Angela?

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Where's Angela?

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Dwight.

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Hello.

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
What does it matter with you?

15
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Would you get Angela, please?

16
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Angela from accounting?

17
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Yes, please.

18
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,000
I'll go look for her.

19
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Movie Monday started with training videos, but we went through those pretty fast.

20
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Then we watched a medical video.

21
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Since then, it's been half our installments of various movies,

22
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
with the exception of an episode of Entourage, which Michael made us watch six times.

23
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Entourage!

24
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:49,000
There you are.

25
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Michael wants everyone inside for Movie Monday.

26
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
I don't care. He's wasting everyone's time.

27
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
No, he's not. Michael knows exactly what he's doing.

28
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,000
How can you say that?

29
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:03,000
He was the top salesman in this company's history. I'll never even come close to matching his numbers.

30
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
He's not a salesman anymore.

31
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:14,000
In my opinion, a good manager protects his employees from verbal abuse and manhandling.

32
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Like you would do if you were manager.

33
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Well, maybe not all manhandling.

34
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Kevin, would you like to do the scenes from last week?

35
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Yes.

36
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Why him? Don't whine. Get the windows.

37
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Previously on Varsity Blues.

38
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Okay, Billy Bob got a head injury, but Coach made him play.

39
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:54,000
So then Lance, he gets sacked, and he's out for the year.

40
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Hello?

41
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Not everyone approves of Movie Monday. I won't say who.

42
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:05,000
I don't approve. I don't.

43
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Hello?

44
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Let's go after that time man. Let's go, let's go. Let's go.

45
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Hey, man. Hope you're back to the milk beds.

46
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:29,000
How would a movie increase productivity, Michael? How on earth would it do that?

47
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
People work faster after.

48
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Magically?

49
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:37,000
No. They have to, to make up for the time they lost watching the movie.

50
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
No.

51
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Kitchen.

52
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Michael is going to get us all fired. You sat back and let him play that dumb movie, and now Jan has peeped off and we're all going to lose our jobs.

53
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,000
That's not going to happen.

54
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
You know she has it out for him now.

55
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
That's not his fault. He had to follow his heart.

56
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Ever since Michael dumped Jan for Carol, Jan's been bitching out on him. Reject a woman and she will never let it go, one of the many defects of their kind. Also weak arms.

57
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Dwight, you should be running this office.

58
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Michael would never let me.

59
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
It's not up to Michael. It's Jan's call. Talk to her.

60
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
I can never do that.

61
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Fine. Sit back and do nothing and let us all get fired.

62
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:36,000
I know that patience and loyalty are good and virtuous traits, but sometimes I just think you need to grow a pair.

63
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:47,000
The shrewts are a very loyal breed, but I also have Mannheim blood from my German grandmother, and the Mannheims knew when to cut and run. No sense going down with a losing regime.

64
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:55,000
But the shrewt blood, it's amazing that when these two bloods mixed, that the whole thing didn't exist.
